parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries to occupants, including cuts, burns, contusions, and permanent damage to vision, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
airbags deploy while the vehicle is stationary
airbags deploy without a crash or collision
windshield breaks due to airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a collision can increase the risk of injury to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash or collision
occupants are injured due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster mounting bolts can cause a sudden loss of braking, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: Snapping sound when applying the brake
sudden loss of braking with the pedal extended to the floor
loud crunching noise when applying the brake
brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle continues to accelerate when parking with foot on brake pedal
intermittent acceleration.

the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is difficult to drive

symptoms: The transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission slips or jumps into gear
the vehicle hesitates or lags when shifting
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is difficult to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The speedometer inaccuracy can cause the driver to unknowingly exceed speed limits, which can lead to safety risks, accidents, and traffic violations.
